comments[11]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T22:03:50.226Z",codex-root,"Scope note 2026-07-13: when pm-ju83 lands, extend this task's SDK reference and migration work with relationship-kind registration, immutable relationship events, bounded adjacency/path/closure/impact queries, cursor and streaming contracts, compact CLI and MCP projections, explain/cost envelopes, legacy-kind migration, and shell pipeline examples. Link implementation docs to pm-96h7 and validate with the existing docs gates."
  "2026-07-17T13:10:37.141Z",codex-root,"Documentation progress: SDK and relationship-graph references now cover public actionability, workspace assembly, semantic traversal, governance findings, layering boundaries, and a non-PM domain reuse pattern. Docs gate passes."
  "2026-07-17T13:47:20.846Z",codex-root,"Verification evidence: linked docs-skills gate passed; SDK and relationship graph docs explain public actionability, assembly, semantic traversal, governance findings, layering, VCS/company reuse, bounds, and migration semantics. Strict 100% docstring coverage, docs links, package tarball, and runnable installed SDK examples pass. This documentation tranche is complete; the task remains open because its acceptance follows every future promoted primitive in pm-usfg/pm-ju83."
  "2026-07-18T14:35:45.096Z",codex-root,"Documentation tranche start 2026-07-18: add the public transaction API, crash/recovery semantics, migration guidance, and runnable VCS example; future promoted primitives remain outside this tranche."
  "2026-07-18T15:19:23.299Z",codex-root,"Documentation tranche evidence: docs/SDK.md now specifies the public transaction contract, recovery transitions, extension-host binding, logical-atomicity boundary, caller idempotency obligations, and VCS example. pm-vcs README/GAP_REPORT document the consumer and close the explicit transaction waiver. Docs/skills, link-facing build, docstring, and packed-package gates passed. Broader SDK reference work remains open after this tranche."
  "2026-07-20T09:59:55.543Z",codex-20260720,"SDK documentation tranche: documented typed atomic transactions, full-item stdin round trips, compact/full output controls, public runtime/error primitives, CLI/MCP parity, and package-author guidance. Docs/links gates and packed SDK import proof passed; this rolling item remains open for later SDK tranches."
  "2026-07-21T16:59:01.853Z",codex-derived-context-20260721,"Linked-test maintenance 2026-07-21: removed stale pnpm docs:links:check entry because that package script no longer exists; current canonical link validation is pnpm quality:docs-links and remains linked alongside quality:docs-skills. This prevents future agents from executing an obsolete command while preserving equivalent stricter coverage."
  "2026-07-21T16:59:34.113Z",codex-derived-context-20260721,"Documentation tranche 2026-07-21: docs/SDK.md now lists the public signal-store exports and contracts and includes a runnable installed-consumer flow using public settings/status-registry primitives; docs/PERFORMANCE.md specifies versioned cursor snapshots, atomic rebuild behavior, scan fallback, and explicit diagnostics. Docs/skills and link gates pass. This rolling item remains open for later promoted primitives."
  "2026-07-21T17:50:57.128Z",codex-derived-context-20260721,"PR #633 exact-head closeout: SDK and performance references document public context signal contracts, rebuild/fallback semantics, diagnostics, and a runnable installed-consumer flow; docs gates are green at 90ef2974. This rolling reference item remains open for future promoted SDK primitives."
  "2026-07-21T18:46:52.152Z",codex-root,"Implementation start: actively documenting the public SDK derived-index projection primitive and its relationship to graph/context cache freshness. Duplicate check reused the existing documentation lineage after all-status inventory; no new documentation item created."
  "2026-07-21T19:26:19.961Z",codex-root,"Documentation tranche evidence: docs/PERFORMANCE.md documents the 500-item activation, small manifest, shared cursor, collapsed atomic delta, cross-process lock, compaction, failure invalidation, and public SDK host contract; docs/RELATIONSHIP_GRAPH.md connects that freshness protocol to graph fingerprints and recovery. Docs/skills and link gates pass, and the public SDK barrel export is verified. This rolling reference item remains open for later promoted primitives."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-18T10:06:40.159Z",maintainer-agent,"Documentation-target expansion 2026-07-18 (PR#587): the promoted-primitive set this reference must cover grew by the SDK relationship event platform — registerRelationshipKinds/RelationshipKindRegistry (extension-contributed kinds with direction/inverse/ordering/cardinality/lifecycle/aliases/version), RelationshipEventLog/RelationshipEventStore bounded immutable streams + reducer projections (in-memory and durable, checkpoint boundary semantics), workspace graph assembly merging active package ontologies, and host-bound SDK injection into extension command handlers (context.sdk with caller authorship). PR#587 seeded docs/SDK.md + docs/EXTENSIONS.md deltas and packages/pm-vcs/README.md is the runnable exemplar to cite; this item still owns the consolidated reference + migration notes. Prior-tranche targets unchanged (graph/analytics + governance subpath modules from PR#579/#580/#581)."
